places:
    place-kings-landing:
        name: "King's Landing"
        type: city
        parent: place-the-crownlands
        properties:
            also_known_as: "The Capital"
            seat_of: "The Iron Throne"
        notes: "Capital of the Seven Kingdoms, home to roughly half a million people. Situated where the Blackwater Rush meets Blackwater Bay on the eastern coast. Founded by Aegon the Conqueror atop Aegon's High Hill, where he raised the Aegonfort. The city sprawls across three great hills: Aegon's High Hill (the Red Keep), Visenya's Hill (the Great Sept of Baelor), and Rhaenys's Hill (the Dragonpit). Flea Bottom is the poorest quarter — a maze of narrow alleys, pot-shops, and stinking tanneries. The Street of Steel, the Street of Silk, and Fishmonger's Square are notable landmarks. The city stinks of dung, smoke, and corruption. Seven gates pierce the walls: the River Gate (Mud Gate), the King's Gate, the Lion Gate, the Gate of the Gods, the Old Gate, the Dragon Gate, and the Iron Gate."
